                    <ab><persName key="#Princeps" ref="#people/3002">Iordanus</persName> Dei gratia
                            <rs key="#Princeps">princeps</rs>. Hoc scriptum memorie fieri iubeo, ut
                        a me fidelibusque meis constanter credi possit et conservari, quomodo a me
                        ordinatus sit <placeName key="#Villages/settlements" ref="#places/109"
                            >Sancti Gemani</placeName> in <rs key="#Curtes">curte</rs>
                        <rs key="#Abbots">abbatis</rs>
                        <persName key="#Abbots #Personal_rank" ref="#people/2421"
                            >Desiderii</persName> pietatis fama <rs key="#Personal_rank"
                            >venerabilis</rs>, ego vero proclamationem suorum hominum qui <rs
                            key="#Castle">castellus</rs>
                        <placeName key="#Castle" ref="#places/4523">Pedemontem</placeName> habitant
                        facio, quoniam ipsi mihi meisque iniuriam intulerunt, quod minime decuissed,
                        pre <rs key="#Landed_possessions">cetera terras ceterasque
                        possessiones</rs>, quas sub <rs key="#Cartula">cartulam</rs> scripti ab
                        incolis <placeName ref="#places/2795">Aquinatibus</placeName> emerant
                        homines eiusdem abbatis ad hec de <rs key="#Castle">castello</rs> notato
                        nomine <placeName key="#Castle" ref="#places/4514">Terano</placeName> et de
                            <rs key="#Fines">finibus</rs> locorum que infra fines continentur, quod
                            <rs key="#parentOf">genitori</rs> meo atque simul mihi sancitum et ac
                        ratum est. In <orgName key="#Monasteries" ref="#juridical_persons/84">Sancti
                            Benedicti</orgName>
                        <rs key="#Monasteries">cenobio</rs> quoque autem Aquinates nostri
                        querimoniam agere studebant abbati de <rs key="#Castle">opido</rs> nomine
                            <placeName key="#Castle" ref="#places/4525">Sarracinisco</placeName>,
                        quoniam ipse habas cum antecessoribus suis cum pace et sine querela
                        habuerunt et adhuc retinet hic. Postea vero cum a <rs
                            key="#Intercessory #Monks">monachorum</rs> collegia ab ipsoque abbate
                        humiliter <rs key="#Intercessory">rogatus</rs> fuissem, ne contra eum neque
                        sibi contra subditos quicquam malivolentie machinari velle, nec mei mecum,
                        quod a me ab aversariorum incursum muniri et defensari debent. Ideo quod
                        bonum et utile hoc fuisse cognoveram, presentibus istis, videlicet <persName
                            key="#Witness"><name ref="Gherardus de Ravannela">Girardo de
                                Ravennela</name></persName>, <persName key="#Witness"
                            ref="#people/4206">Rotberto de Labolita</persName>, <persName
                            key="#Witness"><name ref="Wilielmus de Sancto Laudo">Guillemo de Sancto
                                Laudo</name></persName>, et cum his <rs key="#Bishops">episcopo</rs>
                        <persName key="#Witness #Bishops" ref="#people/4207">Ambrosio</persName>
                        <placeName key="#Bishops" ref="#places/2856">Terracinense</placeName>, <rs
                            key="#Prevosts">preposito</rs> autem <persName ref="#people/2416"
                            key="#Witness #Prevosts">Oderisio</persName>, <persName
                            key="#Witness #Prevosts" ref="#people/4208">Iohanne</persName>
                        <rs key="#Prevosts">preposito</rs>
                        <orgName ref="#juridical_persons/2321">Sancti Benedicti Capuensis</orgName>,
                        a quibusdam astantibus <rs key="#Witness #Monks">monachis</rs>, cum
                            <persName ref="#people/3064" key="#Witness #Judge">Iohanne
                            Capuensi</persName>
                        <rs key="#Judge">iudice</rs> misso a <rs key="#Princeps">principe</rs>
                        <persName key="#Princeps #parentOf" ref="#people/3001">Richardo</persName>,
                        quod virga ei condonavi et omnem malivolentiam et nostram quam contra
                        homines Pedemontis diu memorie commendaveram, eademque traditione
                        hereditates, quarum prius mentionem feci, eisdem qui eas prius quam
                                <persName><name ref="Wilielmus de Menterolo">Guillelmus de
                                Menterolo</name></persName> inde finem daret cum abbate emerant
                        tempore Guillelmi antecessorum, quas dato fine cum abbate emerunt, non a me
                        conceditur. Illos igitur qui castellum Saraciniscum habitant, ut supra
                        dictum est, cum pace et quiete esse concedo, exceptis duobus hominibus,
                        quorum alter habitat Teramus, nomine <persName><name ref="Iohannes"
                                >Iohannes</name></persName>, alter autem <placeName
                            ref="#places/4524">Plumbarolium</placeName>, nomine <persName><name
                                ref="Petrucius">Petrucium</name></persName>. Siquis autem, superbia
                        elatus vel contumeliam constituta, hic infringere laboraverit, sese reum
                        abbato Casini Montis dandum certam emendationem sciat, videlicet <rs
                            key="#Penalty">centum auri libras</rs>. Quatenus servetur, precipio
                        omnibus hec dicta conservare. Hanc paginam manu propria confirmatam sigilli
                        nostri notamine iussimus inprimi. <persName key="#Writer"><name
                                ref="Wilielmus">Guillemus</name></persName>.</ab>
